--------------------------------------------------
SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS: Partial correlation controlling mean accuracy
--------------------------------------------------
NOTE: Binary SD is constrained by mean: SD = sqrt[p*(1-p)]
Partial correlation removes this mathematical artifact.

PARTIAL CORRELATION r(SD_conf, SD_acc | mean_acc):
  Partial r = 0.2135
  p-value = 0.033838
  df = 97

INTERPRETATION:
  Neither correlation is significant
  → No evidence for variability relationship

